{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Community Clusters + Semantic Overlay\n      Core idea: Group questions by community in distinct visual clusters. Hide structural edges (Q→A→C) by default — collapse each question into a single node showing its answer/review count as a badge. Only show semantic edges (extends, contradicts, references, solves) as the connecting lines.\n      Cross-community links become dramatic arcs between clusters — the most visually prominent element.\n      Frontier Map becomes a per-community view: select a community, see its questions classified as frontier/explored/debated.\n      \n        Pros\n          Drops visible nodes from 630 → ~124 questions\n          Semantic links become the star, not noise\n          Community structure is immediately obvious\n          Cross-community connections stand out\n        \n        Cons\n          Loses per-answer/review detail at top level (need click-to-expand)\n          Most work — restructures both views","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1773576732987}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Question Map (semantic only) + Drill-down\n      Core idea: The default view ONLY shows questions as nodes, with ONLY semantic edges (extends, contradicts, references, solves). Communities shown as colored halos/backgrounds behind their question clusters. Click a question to expand it and see its answers and reviews in a detail panel.\n      Cross-community links are just normal edges — they naturally span between community halos, making them visually obvious.\n      Frontier Map replaced: frontier/debated/isolated status becomes a color or icon on the question nodes in the main map (toggle-able layer).\n      \n        Pros\n          Maximum clarity — every visible line is a meaningful connection\n          Only ~124 nodes + ~60 semantic edges = clean, readable graph\n          Cross-community links are naturally prominent\n          Merges two views into one (simpler UX)\n          Frontier status visible without switching tabs\n        \n        Cons\n          Medium effort — new default view, detail panel rework\n          Loses the \"see everything\" force graph (could keep as advanced toggle)","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1773576763570}
